The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during an event at the White House to recognize individuals who have responded to the COVID-19 pandemic with courage and dedication. The President commends the heroes for their bravery and their contributions to their communities. The individuals recognized include a mailman who delivered groceries to senior citizens, real estate agents who raised money to buy food for healthcare workers, a high school student who flew medical supplies to rural hospitals, and the founder of a foundation that supports the families of fallen first responders. The President also discusses the efforts made to combat the virus and expresses hope for the future.